title: Bound Print
medium: Letterpress, etching and aquatint, brush and watercolor on white wove paper mounted on heavy cream board, lines ruled in color and gold paint
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of the Council
description: Interior of large round sitting room with large crystal chandelier, red drapes with gold trim, a fireplace with large mirror and two candelabra on mantel, two windows at left. Walls are white with painted gold ornamentation. Five figures have entered the room: tall woman (mother), flanked by her two daughters, a young man (groom), and a young woman (bride).

tombstone.epitaph:
Bound Print.
Letterpress, etching and aquatint, brush and watercolor on white wove paper mounted on heavy cream board, lines ruled in color and gold paint. Museum purchase through gift of the Council. 1951-128-1-51.
